  "content": "<p>3\ufe0f\u20e35\ufe0f\u20e3 Here&#39;s the 35th post highlighting key new features of the upcoming v258 release of systemd. <a href=\"https://mastodon.social/tags/systemd258\" class=\"mention hashtag\" rel=\"tag\">#<span>systemd258</span></a> </p><p>In various stateless situations it makes sense to boot directly into a root file system that is downloaded as part of the boot process and placed into system RAM. With v258 there&#39;s now native support for this: a new rd.systemd.pull= kernel command line option may be used to download DDIs or tarballs into a tmpfs, optionally authenticate them, and then boot into them.</p>",
